OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Thu 25 Jun to Sat 4 JulFThe
OL,6,Ffirst part of this period will see
OL,7,Fhigh pressure relinquish its grip on
OL,8,Fthe UK with low pressure becoming
OL,9,Fincreasingly dominant for a time.
OL,10,FInitially, most places will start
OL,11,Fmainly fine and dry and it will be hot
OL,12,For very hot and humid across many
OL,13,Fcentral and southern parts. However,
OL,14,Fincreasing amounts of cloud and some
OL,15,Fheavy, thundery rain or showers will
OL,16,Fspread erratically east or northeast
OL,17,Facross all parts, with much cooler,
OL,18,Ffresher conditions eventually
OL,19,Fspreading east or northeast by the end
OL,20,Fof the month. By early July it remains
OL,21,Ffinely balanced as to whether low
OL,22,Fpressure, and more changeable
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Fconditions, are allowed to take over,
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,For whether more settled conditions
OL,25,Fhold sway.
FL,164,160,301,260,100,100
PN,16303
SC,0003
CT,20,T
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F163A1781963310
OL,1,Wj5hw1~{4k7juhw1{$             G3/3
OL,2,W+.-'"-$/*%*%*%/"-$/*%Q,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Sun 5 Jul to Sun 19 Jul
OL,6,FHigh pressure patterns are looking
OL,7,Fslightly more likely than low pressure
OL,8,Fpatterns during this period, meaning
OL,9,Fsettled and drier than average
OL,10,Fconditions are a little more probable
OL,11,Fthan not. There is still a chance of
OL,12,Fsome changeable or more unsettled
OL,13,Fconditions developing at times, with a
OL,14,Frisk of some heavy and thundery
OL,15,Fshowers. Temperatures are likely to be
OL,16,Fabove normal, with a greater than
OL,17,Fnormal chance of hot conditions
OL,18,Fdeveloping at times.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
